WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.480
number three this evening, Psalm 3.

00:00:02.480 --> 00:00:07.360
And last week we started a four-part series from Psalm 3.

00:00:07.360 --> 00:00:09.659
And I mentioned to you that there are eight verses

00:00:09.659 --> 00:00:11.319
in this particular psalm,

00:00:11.319 --> 00:00:14.600
and really four divisions, two verses each.

00:00:14.600 --> 00:00:17.559
And so last week we looked at verses one and two.

00:00:17.559 --> 00:00:21.600
And as we examined the first two verses of Psalm 3,

00:00:21.600 --> 00:00:26.139
we saw the reality of the situation that David faced.

00:00:26.139 --> 00:00:27.719
You'll remember that this psalm,

00:00:27.719 --> 00:00:30.100
if you think about the background of this psalm

00:00:30.100 --> 00:00:31.719
and the setting for this psalm,

00:00:31.719 --> 00:00:35.659
was during the time of Absalom's rebellion and his revolt.

00:00:35.659 --> 00:00:38.779
And as we begin to notice and look back

00:00:38.779 --> 00:00:41.299
at 2 Samuel 15 and 16,

00:00:41.299 --> 00:00:45.020
and look through those chapters that record for us

00:00:45.020 --> 00:00:49.240
the event that David is going through,

00:00:49.240 --> 00:00:52.099
we will find that as we look at this text of scripture,

00:00:52.099 --> 00:00:56.040
this is not an exaggeration on the part of David.

00:00:56.040 --> 00:01:00.099
This is not some type of an assumption

00:01:00.099 --> 00:01:02.340
on the part of David.

00:01:02.340 --> 00:01:03.979
We find that this is reality.

00:01:03.979 --> 00:01:05.279
This is what he was facing.

00:01:05.279 --> 00:01:06.940
This is what he was dealing with.

00:01:06.940 --> 00:01:08.580
We find that it was in verse number one

00:01:08.580 --> 00:01:12.860
that he says, they are increased that trouble me.

00:01:12.860 --> 00:01:14.500
They are increased that trouble me.

00:01:14.500 --> 00:01:16.260
He says again in verse number one,

00:01:16.260 --> 00:01:19.139
we used it as the title of the message last week,

00:01:19.139 --> 00:01:23.680
many are they that rise up against me.

00:01:23.699 --> 00:01:26.580
And so they've increased those that trouble me.

00:01:26.580 --> 00:01:29.019
There are many that rise up against me.

00:01:29.019 --> 00:01:31.779
We find that he said this in verse number two,

00:01:31.779 --> 00:01:34.220
that they were saying of David,

00:01:34.220 --> 00:01:38.139
there is no help for him in God.

00:01:38.139 --> 00:01:41.019
God's not even gonna be able to help him in this situation.

00:01:41.019 --> 00:01:45.059
I'm thankful that our God is a very present help

00:01:45.059 --> 00:01:46.940
in the time of trouble, amen.

00:01:46.940 --> 00:01:48.739
I'm thankful that the Bible tells us,

00:01:48.739 --> 00:01:50.459
lift up our eyes into the hills

00:01:50.459 --> 00:01:51.739
from whence cometh our help.

00:01:51.760 --> 00:01:53.760
Our help cometh from the Lord,

00:01:53.760 --> 00:01:56.199
which made heaven and earth.

00:01:56.199 --> 00:01:59.160
And not only is he able to help,

00:01:59.160 --> 00:02:01.400
but he is available to help.

00:02:01.400 --> 00:02:04.480
And I'm so thankful for the truth of God's word

00:02:04.480 --> 00:02:07.379
with regard to that statement,

00:02:07.379 --> 00:02:10.820
that reality of the help that God provides.

00:02:10.820 --> 00:02:14.779
As we think about the truth of this passage of scripture

00:02:14.779 --> 00:02:17.279
being a reality, not an exaggeration,

00:02:17.279 --> 00:02:20.800
not a possibility that they're going to rise against me,

00:02:20.820 --> 00:02:25.399
but a reality, it was told to us in 2 Samuel 15,

00:02:25.399 --> 00:02:26.720
and verse number 12,

00:02:26.720 --> 00:02:29.399
and the conspiracy was strong

00:02:29.399 --> 00:02:34.399
for the people increased continually with Absalom.

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:37.360
We find that this was the situation

00:02:37.360 --> 00:02:38.919
in which David was facing,

00:02:38.919 --> 00:02:40.380
and it was a real situation.

00:02:40.380 --> 00:02:43.440
The reality is painted, is provided to us

00:02:43.440 --> 00:02:44.979
in verses one and two.

00:02:44.979 --> 00:02:47.240
This evening, as we examine and continue

00:02:47.240 --> 00:02:48.559
through the portion of scripture,

00:02:48.559 --> 00:02:50.479
we'll look at verses three and four,

00:02:51.160 --> 00:02:53.839
and really we'll consider tonight the response,

00:02:53.839 --> 00:02:56.759
David's response to the situation.

00:02:56.759 --> 00:02:59.160
We see the reality last week,

00:02:59.160 --> 00:03:02.820
but I mentioned even as we closed last Wednesday evening,

00:03:02.820 --> 00:03:06.320
that certainly we face troubles, we face difficulties.

00:03:06.320 --> 00:03:09.679
There are people that will oppose those of us

00:03:09.679 --> 00:03:12.339
as we will stand for biblical truth.

00:03:12.339 --> 00:03:14.080
We will face opposition.

00:03:14.080 --> 00:03:15.880
There are many adversaries.

00:03:15.880 --> 00:03:16.839
We understand that.

00:03:16.839 --> 00:03:18.279
We read the word of God,

00:03:18.279 --> 00:03:20.320
and we understand that every time

00:03:21.160 --> 00:03:22.759
someone attempts to do something for God,

00:03:22.759 --> 00:03:24.479
there's going to be opposition.

00:03:24.479 --> 00:03:26.479
There's going to be adversity.

00:03:27.399 --> 00:03:29.779
But how do we respond to that opposition?

00:03:29.779 --> 00:03:33.479
How is it that we respond to the adversity that we face?

00:03:33.479 --> 00:03:38.080
How is it that we respond to those that would trouble us,

00:03:38.080 --> 00:03:40.119
those that would speak ill of us?

00:03:40.119 --> 00:03:41.080
What is it that we do?

00:03:41.080 --> 00:03:42.779
How is it that we respond?

00:03:42.779 --> 00:03:44.979
And tonight, we'll deal with the response

00:03:44.979 --> 00:03:47.020
of David to this situation.

00:03:47.020 --> 00:03:48.919
I would say this, in a single word,

00:03:48.919 --> 00:03:51.320
his response is one of prayer.

00:03:51.320 --> 00:03:55.639
And that's a simple way of looking at verses three and four.

00:03:55.639 --> 00:03:58.000
If you are taking notes and want a title

00:03:58.000 --> 00:03:59.360
for the message this evening,

00:03:59.360 --> 00:04:01.119
it would be from verse number four.

00:04:01.119 --> 00:04:04.800
I cried unto the Lord, and He heard me.

00:04:04.800 --> 00:04:08.800
I cried unto the Lord, and He heard me.

00:04:08.800 --> 00:04:11.000
As we look at this passage of Scripture,

00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:13.160
I want you to notice in the response,

00:04:13.160 --> 00:04:15.320
look at verse three and four, the Bible says,

00:04:15.399 --> 00:04:20.399
but thou, O Lord, art a shield for me,

00:04:21.119 --> 00:04:26.119
my glory and the lifter up of mine head.

00:04:26.119 --> 00:04:29.440
I cried unto the Lord with my voice,

00:04:29.440 --> 00:04:34.440
and He heard me out of His holy hill, Sila.

00:04:35.519 --> 00:04:37.640
As we look at these verses of Scripture

00:04:37.640 --> 00:04:40.920
and consider the response of David to the situation,

00:04:40.920 --> 00:04:42.459
I want you to notice, first of all,

00:04:42.540 --> 00:04:46.859
that David rehearses who God is to him.

00:04:46.859 --> 00:04:50.179
In this act of rehearsing, in verse number three,

00:04:50.179 --> 00:04:53.739
as he rehearses, it's really a reminder to himself.

00:04:53.739 --> 00:04:57.019
And oftentimes as we pray, we've often mentioned,

00:04:57.019 --> 00:04:58.899
I've said, and I've encouraged,

00:04:58.899 --> 00:05:01.940
and I've even revealed to you personally

00:05:01.940 --> 00:05:04.179
how in my own prayer time,

00:05:04.179 --> 00:05:08.179
how I begin my prayer time with a time of adoration,

00:05:08.179 --> 00:05:10.380
praising God for who He is.

00:05:10.380 --> 00:05:12.579
And also not only who He is

00:05:12.579 --> 00:05:14.660
and His attributes and His character,

00:05:14.660 --> 00:05:16.619
but really who He is to me.

00:05:16.619 --> 00:05:19.220
And we begin to consider oftentimes

00:05:19.220 --> 00:05:20.380
throughout the Scriptures,

00:05:20.380 --> 00:05:24.100
we find that He is my advocate.

00:05:24.100 --> 00:05:25.540
He is my shepherd.

00:05:25.540 --> 00:05:27.299
He is my forerunner.

00:05:27.299 --> 00:05:29.220
He is my great high priest.

00:05:29.220 --> 00:05:30.739
We begin to think about these things,

00:05:30.739 --> 00:05:32.820
and as we rehearse those things,

00:05:32.820 --> 00:05:36.140
we're reminding ourselves of who God is to us.

00:05:36.140 --> 00:05:38.179
I'm thankful that He's my Savior,

00:05:38.179 --> 00:05:41.019
and I'm thankful that He is the Savior of the world,

00:05:41.019 --> 00:05:42.179
but you think about the truth

00:05:42.179 --> 00:05:44.579
that He's my Savior personally,

00:05:44.579 --> 00:05:47.380
and David, we find in verse number three,

00:05:47.380 --> 00:05:51.940
he says, but thou, O Lord, are a shield for me,

00:05:51.940 --> 00:05:54.260
my glory and the lifter up of mine head.

00:05:54.260 --> 00:05:56.339
So we find that in verse number three,

00:05:56.339 --> 00:05:59.380
we spoke that his response is one of prayer,

00:05:59.380 --> 00:06:00.820
that he's praying.

00:06:00.820 --> 00:06:02.179
We see that in verse number four,

00:06:02.179 --> 00:06:03.779
he says, I cried unto the Lord.

00:06:03.779 --> 00:06:05.859
But we notice in verse number three

00:06:05.859 --> 00:06:09.019
as he speaks about who God is to him,

00:06:09.019 --> 00:06:10.980
I want you to consider this evening

00:06:10.980 --> 00:06:14.220
that as we respond to situations

00:06:14.220 --> 00:06:17.220
such as what David was facing,

00:06:17.220 --> 00:06:19.100
that which he was dealing with,

00:06:19.100 --> 00:06:20.940
when we deal with adversity,

00:06:20.940 --> 00:06:22.540
when we deal with opposition,

00:06:22.540 --> 00:06:25.019
when we deal with trouble and trials,

00:06:25.019 --> 00:06:27.179
when we respond in prayer,

00:06:27.179 --> 00:06:31.980
when we respond by first rehearsing who God is to me,

00:06:31.980 --> 00:06:35.220
when we recognize and remind ourselves

00:06:35.220 --> 00:06:37.980
of who He is, it's encouraging.

00:06:37.980 --> 00:06:41.179
It encourages us, it strengthens us,

00:06:41.179 --> 00:06:44.859
and it helps us to shift our focus.

00:06:44.859 --> 00:06:48.540
Sometimes what happens in the time of trial,

00:06:48.540 --> 00:06:51.660
in the time of trouble, in the time of difficulty,

00:06:51.660 --> 00:06:55.980
is that all we can focus upon is that trouble, right?

00:06:55.980 --> 00:06:57.420
It just consumes us,

00:06:57.420 --> 00:07:01.899
and we just are so focused upon the trouble and the trial

00:07:01.899 --> 00:07:04.140
and the opposition and the adversity,

00:07:04.140 --> 00:07:06.940
and it sucks all of our attention and all of our time,

00:07:06.940 --> 00:07:10.220
and we're so focused on those things.

00:07:10.220 --> 00:07:12.540
And when we begin to pray,

00:07:12.540 --> 00:07:16.739
we begin to rehearse who God is to us,

00:07:16.739 --> 00:07:18.980
it's a shift in focus.

00:07:18.980 --> 00:07:21.660
No longer am I focusing on woe is me,

00:07:21.660 --> 00:07:26.260
no longer am I focusing on my problem, my trouble, my trial,

00:07:26.260 --> 00:07:28.779
but we find that here in Psalm 3,

00:07:28.779 --> 00:07:31.940
as David understands the reality of the situation

00:07:31.940 --> 00:07:33.059
in the first two verses,

00:07:33.059 --> 00:07:35.100
his response is one of prayer,

00:07:35.100 --> 00:07:39.820
and he begins that prayer by rehearsing who God is to him.

00:07:39.820 --> 00:07:44.820
First of all, he says that He is a shield for me.

00:07:44.980 --> 00:07:48.140
But thou, O Lord, verse number three,

00:07:48.140 --> 00:07:51.820
art a shield for me.

00:07:51.820 --> 00:07:53.940
Oftentimes throughout the book of Psalms,

00:07:53.940 --> 00:07:56.700
we find that the Word of God teaches us

00:07:56.700 --> 00:08:01.260
and reveals to us that our God is a shield and a buckler.

00:08:01.260 --> 00:08:04.299
We find that this is the first reference

00:08:04.299 --> 00:08:09.019
of God being a shield for me in the book of Psalms.

00:08:09.019 --> 00:08:11.540
And we find that David, as he says,

00:08:11.540 --> 00:08:13.100
as he makes this declaration,

00:08:13.100 --> 00:08:15.579
as he rehearses who God is to him,

00:08:15.579 --> 00:08:20.540
when he reminds himself that God, Jehovah, the Creator,

00:08:20.540 --> 00:08:22.500
the King of kings, the Lord of lords,

00:08:22.500 --> 00:08:27.500
that He is a shield for me.

00:08:27.739 --> 00:08:29.299
Think about that.

00:08:29.299 --> 00:08:32.059
I mean, he's dealing with great adversity.

00:08:32.059 --> 00:08:34.900
Remember, those that were increased,

00:08:34.900 --> 00:08:36.059
that were troubling him,

00:08:36.059 --> 00:08:37.820
we find that he said there were many

00:08:37.820 --> 00:08:39.419
that rise up against him.

00:08:39.419 --> 00:08:41.539
It says that in verse number two,

00:08:41.539 --> 00:08:43.940
that those enemies were saying of him

00:08:43.940 --> 00:08:46.659
that there is no help for him in God.

00:08:46.659 --> 00:08:49.940
And we find that David, he responds,

00:08:49.940 --> 00:08:51.940
though the conspiracy was strong

00:08:51.940 --> 00:08:55.700
and though the people increased continually with Absalom,

00:08:55.700 --> 00:08:58.739
we find that he begins to remind himself

00:08:58.739 --> 00:09:00.219
as he rehearses and he says,

00:09:00.219 --> 00:09:04.340
Lord, Thou art a shield for me.

00:09:04.340 --> 00:09:06.099
What does a shield do?

00:09:06.099 --> 00:09:08.059
A shield provides defense.

00:09:08.940 --> 00:09:10.979
A shield provides protection.

00:09:12.020 --> 00:09:15.099
And we think about the imagery

00:09:15.099 --> 00:09:17.700
and we think about the understanding

00:09:17.700 --> 00:09:20.340
as David is praying and he's rehearsing

00:09:20.340 --> 00:09:21.659
who God is to him,

00:09:21.659 --> 00:09:26.659
he begins by saying, Lord, you're my shield.

00:09:27.619 --> 00:09:32.619
Lord, you art a shield for me.

00:09:33.140 --> 00:09:36.780
I love the fact that he says for me

00:09:36.780 --> 00:09:38.219
because it's personal.

00:09:39.299 --> 00:09:40.299
It's precious.

00:09:40.299 --> 00:09:42.140
When you think about it in those terms,

00:09:42.140 --> 00:09:44.340
often we've made the statement

00:09:44.340 --> 00:09:46.219
as we've considered the 23rd Psalm,

00:09:46.219 --> 00:09:47.859
the Lord is my shepherd

00:09:47.859 --> 00:09:49.820
and all of the personal pronouns

00:09:49.820 --> 00:09:51.179
that are used by the Psalmist

00:09:51.179 --> 00:09:53.460
in that wonderful, familiar Psalm.

00:09:53.460 --> 00:09:57.780
And we find that that brings great comfort to our hearts.

00:09:57.780 --> 00:10:00.179
It encourages us and it strengthens us.

00:10:00.179 --> 00:10:03.859
And here, as David is rehearsing who God is,

00:10:03.859 --> 00:10:06.219
yes, he's dealing with great adversity,

00:10:06.219 --> 00:10:07.719
with great opposition,

00:10:07.719 --> 00:10:08.479
but he says,

00:10:08.479 --> 00:10:14.119
"...but Thou, O Lord, art a shield for me."

00:10:14.119 --> 00:10:18.439
They may say that there's no help for him in God,

00:10:18.439 --> 00:10:21.399
but God, I know that You're my shield.

00:10:21.399 --> 00:10:23.379
Isn't that precious?

00:10:23.379 --> 00:10:27.099
And we see, do you notice how there's a shift in focus?

00:10:27.099 --> 00:10:28.939
Do we notice how that, yes,

00:10:28.939 --> 00:10:32.619
the reality of the situation is given to us in verses 1 and 2?

00:10:32.619 --> 00:10:34.919
Indeed, this is not just an assumption.

00:10:34.919 --> 00:10:36.919
This is not an exaggeration.

00:10:36.919 --> 00:10:40.799
There was real trouble.

00:10:40.799 --> 00:10:44.599
But instead of being consumed and focused upon just the trouble

00:10:44.599 --> 00:10:48.159
and the many adversaries and all of the problems,

00:10:48.159 --> 00:10:49.399
his attention, why?

00:10:49.399 --> 00:10:51.739
Because he responded in prayer,

00:10:51.739 --> 00:10:55.899
his attention, his focus is shifted not to his problem,

00:10:55.899 --> 00:10:57.739
but to his God.

00:10:57.999 --> 00:11:01.379
And how precious that is.

00:11:01.379 --> 00:11:03.219
Someone said this,

00:11:03.219 --> 00:11:07.099
we need to simply glance at our circumstances,

00:11:07.099 --> 00:11:10.159
but we need to gaze at our Savior.

00:11:10.159 --> 00:11:11.599
And I like that.

00:11:11.599 --> 00:11:13.199
Because Hebrews 12 says,

00:11:13.199 --> 00:11:15.499
"...looking unto Jesus,

00:11:15.499 --> 00:11:18.259
the Author and Finisher of our faith."

00:11:18.259 --> 00:11:23.739
So often, however, we find ourselves as we live this life,

00:11:23.739 --> 00:11:27.579
when we go through difficulties and trials and troubles,

00:11:27.919 --> 00:11:32.219
that we actually gaze upon our problems

00:11:32.219 --> 00:11:35.599
and simply glance at our Savior.

00:11:35.599 --> 00:11:38.319
And how it's not the way it ought to be.

00:11:38.319 --> 00:11:40.399
We think of Peter.

00:11:40.399 --> 00:11:44.599
Often times, we think of Peter when he walked on water.

00:11:44.599 --> 00:11:46.999
What happened when he walked on the water?

00:11:46.999 --> 00:11:49.339
Where was his attention fixed?

00:11:49.339 --> 00:11:52.179
I don't know how many steps he took out of the boat,

00:11:52.179 --> 00:11:55.519
but I find in my sanctified imagination

00:11:55.519 --> 00:11:57.219
as I would look at that scene,

00:11:57.219 --> 00:12:00.959
I find that Peter is zeroed in, he is gazing,

00:12:00.959 --> 00:12:03.459
he is focused upon the Lord Jesus Christ,

00:12:03.459 --> 00:12:04.359
and he says,

00:12:04.359 --> 00:12:09.259
Lord, if it be Thou, bid me come to Thee.

00:12:09.259 --> 00:12:10.799
And what does Jesus say?

00:12:10.799 --> 00:12:12.359
Come.

00:12:12.359 --> 00:12:13.839
And what does Peter do?

00:12:13.839 --> 00:12:15.399
He walks.

00:12:15.399 --> 00:12:17.099
Was the storm raging?

00:12:17.099 --> 00:12:18.839
Were the waves tempestuous?

00:12:18.839 --> 00:12:20.139
Was the wind boisterous?

00:12:20.139 --> 00:12:21.879
Absolutely.

00:12:21.879 --> 00:12:24.619
But he's focused upon Jesus.

00:12:24.619 --> 00:12:26.719
And he walked on water.

00:12:26.819 --> 00:12:29.219
And what happened to Peter?

00:12:29.219 --> 00:12:31.079
His focus changed.

00:12:31.079 --> 00:12:32.279
Right?

00:12:32.279 --> 00:12:33.119
What do you look at?

00:12:33.119 --> 00:12:34.819
Man, the wind, the waves,

00:12:34.819 --> 00:12:37.099
the reality of what he was facing,

00:12:37.099 --> 00:12:39.159
and he began to sink.

00:12:39.159 --> 00:12:40.659
What's the Bible tell us?

00:12:40.659 --> 00:12:41.500
He was wise.

00:12:41.500 --> 00:12:43.099
He said, Lord, help.

00:12:43.099 --> 00:12:45.639
And the Lord graciously brought him up.

00:12:45.639 --> 00:12:47.039
And I believe with all my heart

00:12:47.039 --> 00:12:50.199
that he walked on water back to the boat.

00:12:50.199 --> 00:12:52.299
However far he got out of the ship,

00:12:52.299 --> 00:12:55.679
he had to walk that far back with the Lord.

00:12:55.699 --> 00:12:57.379
And we find that here,

00:12:57.379 --> 00:12:59.000
as we note the response,

00:12:59.000 --> 00:13:01.039
we find that David begins first

00:13:01.039 --> 00:13:05.119
by rehearsing who God is to him.

00:13:05.119 --> 00:13:05.959
