I even mentioned this on Sunday evening

00:30:05.439 --> 00:30:08.539
how many times these writers of these hymns,

00:30:08.539 --> 00:30:11.039
they were greatly impacted and influenced

00:30:11.039 --> 00:30:13.359
through the Word of God.

00:30:13.359 --> 00:30:14.599
As they walked with God,

00:30:14.599 --> 00:30:17.079
as they read and meditated upon the Word of God,

00:30:17.079 --> 00:30:20.079
you can see in the words of the hymns that we sing

00:30:20.079 --> 00:30:22.759
how that God's Word was so instrumental

00:30:22.759 --> 00:30:28.239
in their lives.

00:30:28.239 --> 00:30:31.299
Chapter 567 in our hymnal,

00:30:31.299 --> 00:30:32.459
the title of the song is,

00:30:32.459 --> 00:30:35.059
All Your Anxiety.

00:30:35.059 --> 00:30:38.979
Is there a heart or bound by sorrow?

00:30:38.979 --> 00:30:42.779
Is there a life weighed down by care?

00:30:42.779 --> 00:30:46.379
Come to the cross, each burden bearing,

00:30:46.379 --> 00:30:51.379
all your anxiety, leave it there.

00:30:51.379 --> 00:30:54.059
No other friend so keen to help you.

00:30:54.059 --> 00:30:56.899
No other friend so quick to hear.

00:30:56.899 --> 00:30:59.579
No other place to leave your burden.

00:30:59.579 --> 00:31:03.939
No other one to hear your prayer.

00:31:03.939 --> 00:31:08.539
Come then at once, delay no longer.

00:31:08.539 --> 00:31:11.099
Heed His entreaty, kind and sweet.

00:31:11.099 --> 00:31:13.379
You need not fear a disappointment.

00:31:13.379 --> 00:31:17.379
Ye shall find peace at the mercy seat.

00:31:17.379 --> 00:31:20.899
All your anxiety, all your care,

00:31:20.899 --> 00:31:24.579
bring to the mercy seat, leave it there.

00:31:24.579 --> 00:31:27.939
Never a burden He cannot bear.

00:31:27.939 --> 00:31:32.019
Never a friend like Jesus.

00:31:32.019 --> 00:31:35.699
The last phrase of the third verse of this song

00:31:35.699 --> 00:31:40.259
says you shall find peace at the mercy seat.

00:31:40.259 --> 00:31:43.219
And next week as we study Psalm 3

00:31:43.219 --> 00:31:45.899
and verses 5 and 6,

00:31:45.899 --> 00:31:48.299
the preview as I gave you a preview last week

00:31:48.299 --> 00:31:49.699
to tonight's lesson,

00:31:49.699 --> 00:31:51.939
the preview for next week's lesson,

00:31:51.939 --> 00:31:54.059
is that in 5 and 6 of this psalm,

00:31:54.059 --> 00:31:57.939
in those verses, you see a peace.

00:31:57.939 --> 00:31:59.859
You see a rest.

00:31:59.859 --> 00:32:01.779
And what a blessing.

00:32:01.779 --> 00:32:04.299
Because when we understand who He is to me,

00:32:04.299 --> 00:32:06.899
and I rehearse it, I remind myself,

00:32:06.899 --> 00:32:13.139
Lord, Thou art a shield for me.

00:32:13.139 --> 00:32:18.139
My glory, the lifter up of mine head.

00:32:18.139 --> 00:32:21.939
I cried unto Thee with my voice,

00:32:21.939 --> 00:32:24.419
and He heard me.

00:32:24.419 --> 00:32:27.459
He heard me.

00:32:27.459 --> 00:32:30.299
Out of His holy hill, Sila.

00:32:30.299 --> 00:32:32.779
David, as he's praying,

00:32:32.779 --> 00:32:36.579
as he responds to this difficulty that he's facing,

00:32:36.579 --> 00:32:38.499
it's exemplary for us.

00:32:38.499 --> 00:32:40.499
It's encouraging

00:32:40.499 --> 00:32:43.779
as we see the way that the Lord would sustain him.

00:32:43.779 --> 00:32:45.739
The situation was real.

00:32:45.739 --> 00:32:47.539
This was not a figment of his imagination.

00:32:47.539 --> 00:32:49.619
This was not an exaggeration.

00:32:49.619 --> 00:32:50.939
This was not an embellishment.

00:32:50.939 --> 00:32:55.499
No, this was a real situation he was dealing with.

00:32:55.499 --> 00:32:58.579
But his response is noteworthy.

00:32:58.579 --> 00:33:01.939
And it's summed up in one word, prayer.

00:33:01.939 --> 00:33:04.819
We change our focus from all of our trouble

00:33:04.819 --> 00:33:06.939
and all of our care and all of our burdens,

00:33:06.939 --> 00:33:09.339
and we change our focus from all of that,

00:33:09.339 --> 00:33:12.979
and we get our focus on our Savior

00:33:12.979 --> 00:33:14.939
and who He is to us

00:33:14.939 --> 00:33:19.019
and how it changes the situation.

00:33:19.019 --> 00:33:20.019
Let's pray together.

00:33:20.059 --> 00:33:21.619
We love you.

00:33:21.619 --> 00:33:23.459
We thank you for loving us.

00:33:23.459 --> 00:33:26.019
We thank you for this psalm.

00:33:26.019 --> 00:33:27.299
And I believe this evening

00:33:27.299 --> 00:33:30.339
that as we have the opportunity

00:33:30.339 --> 00:33:34.059
to slowly walk through the verses of this psalm,

00:33:34.059 --> 00:33:36.179
God, You would use it in our hearts and lives

00:33:36.179 --> 00:33:39.259
to encourage us and to strengthen us.

00:33:39.259 --> 00:33:41.419
No doubt, we face difficulties

00:33:41.419 --> 00:33:45.899
and we deal with adversities.

00:33:45.899 --> 00:33:48.499
But God, I thank You

00:33:48.539 --> 00:33:50.539
for those of us that have been born again,

00:33:50.539 --> 00:33:54.219
we're saved, we've been washed in the blood of Jesus Christ.

00:33:54.219 --> 00:33:57.099
You're our Savior, our Helper.

00:33:57.099 --> 00:33:59.099
And we will lift up our eyes into the hills

00:33:59.099 --> 00:34:01.139
from whence cometh our help,

00:34:01.139 --> 00:34:02.779
knowing that You're the Creator

00:34:02.779 --> 00:34:05.779
and the Sustainer of all things.

00:34:05.779 --> 00:34:09.259
God, I'm thankful that You are a shield for me

00:34:09.259 --> 00:34:11.819
just as You were for David.

00:34:11.819 --> 00:34:16.419
You provide the protection and the defense that we need.

00:34:16.419 --> 00:34:19.059
God, I thank You that You're constant, consistent,

00:34:19.059 --> 00:34:21.859
though all of our circumstances can change quickly

00:34:21.859 --> 00:34:25.259
and drastically,

00:34:25.259 --> 00:34:26.939
You remain the same.

00:34:26.939 --> 00:34:28.779
You're our glory.

00:34:28.779 --> 00:34:31.259
The lifter up of mine head,

00:34:31.259 --> 00:34:34.939
though the circumstances can become discouraging.

00:34:34.939 --> 00:34:37.339
God, I thank You

00:34:37.339 --> 00:34:40.659
that You encourage us through Your Word,

00:34:40.659 --> 00:34:41.859
through the Holy Spirit of God,

00:34:41.859 --> 00:34:44.099
through other believers.

00:34:44.099 --> 00:34:45.659
At times, even as David did,

00:34:45.659 --> 00:34:48.979
we have to encourage ourselves in the Lord.

00:34:48.979 --> 00:34:50.779
I pray, God, that You'd bless our time of prayer.

00:34:50.779 --> 00:34:53.299
We thank You for the privilege,

00:34:53.299 --> 00:34:55.979
even as David rejoiced in that next verse of Scripture.

00:34:55.979 --> 00:34:58.659
Why? Because You heard him.

00:34:58.659 --> 00:35:00.659
We understand this evening that when we pray,

00:35:00.659 --> 00:35:03.819
You hear us.

00:35:03.819 --> 00:35:05.659
That You're able to do exceeding abundantly

00:35:05.659 --> 00:35:07.979
above all that we ask or think.

00:35:07.979 --> 00:35:09.779
Bless our time, and we'll thank You for it.

00:35:09.779 --> 00:35:11.779
In Christ's name we pray, amen.

